<h2>Casement Windows</h2>
Casement windows are one of the most popular window styles in the world today. This system has been in existence since the beginning of the 18th century. First constructed out of iron and true leaded divisions, the casement window was only for the very wealthy. However, the industrial revolution changed this due to the introduction of mass production of glass and wooden frames. Today wooden casement windows are still very popular, but will rot, warp, possibly succumb to termites, and require stain or paint maintenance. To avoid these flaws all Solar Innovations<sup>¬Æ</sup> casement windows are made from an aluminum thermal frame, which helps with insulation and protection from the elements.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_single_image image="37079" img_size="full"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
