<h2><img class="aligncenter wp-image-37078 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/casement-residential.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Glazing</h2>
The glazing used in casement windows is insulated tempered glass. There are unlimited choices for the specific glass variation used on your project. A practical choice for glass is a LowE tint. This type of glass helps minimize the amount of UV-rays from penetrating a room. The reduction in UV-rays slows down fading of objects within the room, such as furniture and window treatments. Apply grid work to the windows to achieve a more classic or traditional.

